@cb_doge Compare Artemis II at Liftoff:

Artemis 2 (SLS): ~8.8 million lbf total from 4 liquid engines + 2 massive solid boosters. 

Starship: ~16–18+ million lbf (or more) from the booster's 33 liquid Raptor engines alone. Roughly 1.8–2+ times the thrust of SLS.

